        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-04 14:51:59.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI dont think we want release specific robot files like aai-casablanca-ccvpn.robot. aai-ccvpn.robot or something similar",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "d160b8569026263ce62c8db66e05d18cf7d797b1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-04 14:57:29.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(4 comments)\n\nAAI team wants to expand the robot testcases as per Catherine's presentation at https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/PTL+2019-02-19\n\nShould these be put somewhere else?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "d9bcfe0d67780b59ba8c16b45faf1aeb1ffebc9f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 29,
          "name": "Brian Freeman",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "bf1936@att.com",
          "username": "bdfreeman1421"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-04 15:35:29.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nif the intent is to have a aai-backwards-compatibility-v14.robot function that would get added to each release as the version number increases then I guess you need to create aai-[something]-v14, aai-something]-v16 etc. Not sure these are end to end tests becuase we arent testing that a Dublin vFW works end to end with v14 API's when most components will be calling the v16 APIs. If its simply AAI regression as part of verify/merge CSIT jobs then we should have a nomenclature with CSIT in the filename to distribution End to End tests from CSIT tests. aai-csit-v14 , aai-csit-v11 ?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "2b58ec244123e6fb16bdfbc0d5f4efec76eb1f62",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 37,
          "name": "Daniel Rose",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ultimatedogg@gmail.com",
          "username": "DR695H"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-04 15:38:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\ni looked over catherines presentation. I think if we are going to support csit type tests, i am ok. i think we need to put them in testsuites/<app> and tag those tests as csit. I still also dont think we should put release specific code in here though. I think supporting 2 versions of aai schema is ok if you ar releasing that, but calling something as casablanca is not - the branch should always work with the release it is.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "d8c40486d5c8405c1b5f85c079b58b224afcad1f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-05 00:00:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nAAI team did have an idea that our tests could be used to diagnose installation problems, e.g. pulling the wrong version and wondering why it doesn't work. So as part of the \"sanity integration\" testing, we would publish these tools/scripts for use on any installation (development, test labs, production, etc), not just the latest.\n\nI will update a new patchset.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
